dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="cytoplasm" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">cytoplasm</sd-tag> (L1-L3, cone). CM, <sd-tag id="sdTag57" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="assayed" text="cytoplasmic membrane" ext_ids="GO:0005886" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="plasma membrane" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">cytoplasmic membrane</sd-tag>. The speculated identity of densities in the <sd-tag id="sdTag54" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="assayed" text="archaellum" ext_ids="GO:0097589" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="archaeal-type flagellum" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">archaellum</sd-tag> is proposed: archaellum fiber = <sd-tag id="sdTag59" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="FlaA/B flagellins" ext_ids="Q9V2X0///Q9V2W7///Q9V2W8///Q9V2W9///Q9V2X1" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="flaB2///flaB5///flaB4///flaB3///flaB1" ext_tax_ids="69014///69014///69014///69014///69014" ext_tax_names="Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1///Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1///Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1///Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1///Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot////https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot////https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot////https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot////https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">FlaA/B flagellins</sd-tag>; integral membrane density = <sd-tag id="sdTag69" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="FlaJ" ext_ids="" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="">FlaJ</sd-tag>; L1 = <sd-tag id="sdTag70" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="FlaI" ext_ids="" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="">FlaI</sd-tag>; L2/L3/cone = <sd-tag id="sdTag68" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="FlaH" ext_ids="" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="">FlaH</sd-tag>/<sd-tag id="sdTag67" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="FlaC" ext_ids="Q5JEE9" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="TK0043" ext_tax_ids="69014" ext_tax_names="Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">FlaC</sd-tag>/<sd-tag id="sdTag71" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="assayed" text="D" ext_ids="Q5JEE8" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="TK0044" ext_tax_ids="69014" ext_tax_names="Thermococcus kodakarensis KOD1" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">D</sd-tag>/E.Scale bar 10 nm (applies to A, B). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=34754"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="34755">Figure 4. Structure of the <em>T. kodakaraensis</em> archaellum.<strong>(B)</strong> For comparison, a <sd-tag id="sdTag62" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="subtomogram average" ext_ids="BAO_0002525///BAO_0000455" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="tomography///transmission electron microscopy" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23///https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">subtomogram average</sd-tag> of the <sd-tag id="sdTag63" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="assayed" text="type IVa pilus machine" ext_ids="GO:0009288" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="bacterial-type flagellum" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">type IVa pilus machine</sd-tag> from <sd-tag id="sdTag61" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="organism" role="component" text="Myxococcus xanthus" ext_ids="34" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="Myxococcus xanthus" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy/"><em>Myxococcus xanthus</em></sd-tag> is shown (adapted with permission from [8]). Arrows indicate components with recognized homology. OM, <sd-tag id="sdTag65" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="assayed" text="outer membrane" ext_ids="GO:0019867" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="outer membrane" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">outer membrane</sd-tag>; IM, <sd-tag id="sdTag66" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="subcellular" role="assayed" text="inner membrane" ext_ids="GO:0009276" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="Gram-negative-bacterium-type cell wall" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/">inner membrane</sd-tag>. Scale bar 10 nm (applies to A, B). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=34755"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="11844"><title>.</title><label>Figure 5</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=11844"/><sd-panel panel_id="34749"><strong>Figure 5. Schematic comparing organization of the related <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994163057130" parent-tag-id="24">archaellum</sd-pretag> and type IVa pilus basal bodies.</strong> In the bacterial T4P <strong>(B)</strong>, an integrated system of components spanning the outer and inner membranes (OM, IM) uses the peptidoglycan cell wall (PG) to clamp the ATPase, allowing rotation of PilC (orange) in the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994144187640" parent-tag-id="4">membrane</sd-pretag> to assemble the pilus fiber. In the <em><sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994379693040" parent-tag-id="56">T. kodakaraensis</sd-pretag></em> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994163002890" parent-tag-id="24">archaellum</sd-pretag> <strong>(A)</strong>, our results suggest that an integrated system of components extends from the single <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994144209660" parent-tag-id="4">membrane</sd-pretag> (CM) inward to a large conical structure in the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994151840650" parent-tag-id="10">cytoplasm</sd-pretag> to similarly brace the ATPase. Sensory components (purple) are proposed to be located in the periplasm for the T4P (integrating signals for disassembly) and the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994151840651" parent-tag-id="10">cytoplasm</sd-pretag> for the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14994163295700" parent-tag-id="24">archaellum</sd-pretag> (integrating signals for rotation). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=34749"/></sd-panel></fig></article>